{"source_key":"sha256-9871f21b384df107a3dac33a57efe13d","record_index":27,"record_hash":"sha256:f40551dd4678730fad9bec6cb985cfc62334bb508f1f6753ce4a00f003fcb2f6","timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:21:43.908Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: c73271\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2303\nOutput:\n# Agentlog Sync Lifecycle\n\nThis note sketches a future hidden command:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sync [--remote <name>]\n```\n\nThe command should exchange only GitButler agentlog metadata. Capture remains a\nlocal operation; sync is the explicit lifecycle step that sends captured\nmetadata to a remote and receives metadata captured elsewhere.\n\n## Goals\n\n- Send and receive agentlog metadata through GitMeta refs.\n- Keep the command scoped to agentlog keys, not every shareable GitMeta key.\n- Materialize received metadata back into local SQLite so readers can query it\n  normally.\n- Reuse GitMeta library APIs for serialization, fetch, push, conflict handling,\n  and materialization.\n- Keep hook/capture commands local-only and fast.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- Do not make capture or hooks push metadata.\n- Do not sync unrelated GitMeta namespaces.\n- Do not infer branch or pull request ownership.\n- Do not implement custom Git transport in `but-agentlog`.\n- Do not silently install persistent project filter rules just to make this\n  command work.\n\n## Agentlog Key Scope\n\nAgentlog sync should include:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-sessions\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*\n```\n\nThe first key may appear on the `project` target as the session index and on\nfuture branch/change/commit targets as relationship references. Include both.\nThe durable session data stays on the `project` target.\n\nKeep the matcher exact:\n\n```text\nkey == \"gitbutler:agent-sessions\"\nkey starts with \"gitbutler:agent-session:\"\n```\n\nDo not match broader prefixes such as