e.\n\nFuture GitButler UX can decide whether to run this same sync primitive as:\n\n- manual only\n- part of a GitButler \"sync workspace\" action\n- part of branch/PR publish\n- best-effort background sync for opted-in projects\n\nThat policy should live above `but-agentlog`; the crate should provide a small\nsync primitive and clear result reporting.\n\n## Failure Handling\n\nFor the explicit command:\n\n- missing GitMeta remote should fail clearly\n- missing `refs/meta/agentlog` on an existing remote should create it on push\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:21:43.908Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}